BAKER, Appellant, v. CODDING et al., Respondents. (City Court of New York, General Term. December 22, 1892.) Action by Ebenezer T. Baker against D. Edgar Codding and Osmond H. Atwood. For former report, see 18 N. Y. Supp. 159.

Argued before EHRLICH, C. J., and FITZSIMONS, J.

FITZSIMONS, J.

The two orders appealed from must be affirmed. Upon issuing the execution herein, defendants thereunder required only the collection of the amount of $213.12, not $217.49, as taxed in the judgment roll. This practice is correct. Section 3264, Code. The orders of August 1st and August 15th appealed from are each affirmed, with costs.
